meanings.definition: To make too strong an impression on someone.
meanings.sent2: The movie's special effects really overimpresses the audience.
meanings.sent3: His constant bragging about his achievements overimpresses everyone at the party.
meanings.sent4: The beauty of the sunset overimpresses the painter's senses.
meanings.sent5: The loud noise of the fireworks overimpresses the young child.

meanings.definition: To impress too much or too strongly.
meanings.sent1: The extravagant decorations overimpresses the guests at the party.
meanings.sent2: The grandeur of the palace overimpresses visitors from around the world.
meanings.sent3: The chef's use of exotic spices overimpresses the taste buds of the diners.
meanings.sent4: The athlete's performance overimpresses the coach, leading to high expectations.
meanings.sent5: The size of the skyscraper overimpresses passersby on the street.
